data.enText: not used in the progressive tenses
if sth contains sth else, it has that thing inside it or as part of it

data.chText: 这种饮料不含任何酒精。
data.enText: This drink doesn't contain any alcohol.

data.chText: 她的陈述有一两处不准确。
data.enText: Her statement contained one or two inaccuracies.
a brown envelope containing dollar bills
The bottle contains (= can hold) two litres.
to keep your feelings under control

data.chText: 她无法抑制内心的激动。
data.enText: She was unable to contain her excitement.

data.chText: 我气愤极了，简直无法克制自己。
data.enText: I was so furious I just couldn't contain myself (= I had to express my feelings) .
to prevent sth harmful from spreading or getting worse
Government forces have failed to contain the rebellion.

simple_means.memory_skill: con 加强 + tain 拿住 → 统统拿住 → 包含

ex.enText: This car can hold four people.
How much water does this bottle hold?

synonyms.bx: 指容纳某一数量的人或事物，强调包容的能力。

ex.enText: What is contained in the bottle?

ex.chText: 这个书架上现在有60本书，但它能装下150本。
ex.enText: This bookshelf currently contains 60 books but can hold 150 ones.

ex.chText: 这份报告包含你所需的一切数据。
ex.enText: This report contains all the data you need.

synonyms.bx: 指容器装有具体东西，含仍有剩余空间之意；也指包含具体之物或数据、信息等。

ex.chText: 这辆新车包含了许多改进。
ex.enText: The new car embodies many improvements.

ex.chText: 那项提案包含在决议草案中吗？
ex.enText: Has the proposal been embodied in that draft resolution?

synonyms.bx: 指包含某些内容，而这些内容是某事物的组成部分。

ex.chText: 自然科学包括许多学科。
该理论涉及心理学的不同方面。
ex.enText: This theory embraces different aspects of psychology.

synonyms.bx: 指包含和整体有关的细节。

ex.chText: 她的作品包括小说和散文。
ex.enText: Her writings include novels and prose.

synonyms.bx: 指包括属于整体的部分，可以是具体的或抽象的。

ex.chText: 新员工们需要知道这份工作包括什么。
ex.enText: New employees need to know what the job will involve.

ex.chText: 考试将包括朗读一则新闻。
ex.enText: The test will involve reading a piece of news.

ex.chText: 她没想到写一部小说需要做这么多的工作。
ex.enText: She didn't realize writing a novel involved so much work.

synonyms.bx: 指必然包括某种结果，所接的事物通常是抽象的。

tr: hold back, as of a danger or an enemy
check the expansion or influence of
example: Check the growth of communism in South East Asia
Turn back the tide of communism
A totally new idea is comprised in this paper
The record contains many old songs from the 1930's

tr: be capable of holding or containing
example: This box won't take all the items

value.def: If something such as a box, bag, room, or place contains things, those things are inside it.

example.ex: The bag contained a Christmas card...
example.tran: 这个包里装着一张圣诞卡。

example.ex: Factory shops contain a wide range of cheap furnishings...
example.tran: 工厂车间里陈设着种类繁多的廉价家具。

example.ex: The 77,000-acre estate contains five of the highest peaks in Scotland.
example.tran: 7.7万英亩的私人土地上有5座苏格兰最高的山峰。

value.def: If a substance contains something, that thing is a part of it.

example.ex: Greek yogurt contains much less fat than double cream...
example.tran: 希腊酸奶比高脂浓奶油所含脂肪要少得多。

example.ex: Many cars run on petrol which contains lead.

value.def: If writing, speech, or film contains particular information, ideas, or images, it includes them.

example.ex: This sheet contained a list of problems a patient might like to raise with the doctor...
example.tran: 这张单子列出了病人可能会向医生提出的一系列问题。

example.ex: The two discs also contain two of Britten's lesser-known song-cycles.
example.tran: 这两张唱片还包含了布里顿两首不甚知名的声乐套曲。

value.tran: (著作、讲话或电影中)包括，包含

value.def: If a group or organization contains a certain number of people, those are the people that are in it.

example.ex: The committee contains 11 Democrats and nine Republicans.
example.tran: 这个委员会包括11名民主党人和9名共和党人。

value.def: If you contain something, you control it and prevent it from spreading or increasing.

example.ex: More than a hundred firemen are still trying to contain the fire at the plant...
example.tran: 上百名消防队员仍在试图控制工厂的火势。

example.ex: The city authorities said the curfew had contained the violence.
example.tran: 市政府称宵禁遏制住了暴力事件。

value.def: If you cannot contain a feeling such as excitement or anger, or if you cannot contain yourself, you cannot prevent yourself from showing your feelings.

example.ex: But he was bursting with curiosity, and one day he just couldn't contain himself. 'What are you going to do?' he asked...
example.tran: 但他满心好奇，一天，他真的忍不住了。“你打算做什么？”他问道。

example.ex: Evans could barely contain his delight: 'I'm so proud of her,' he said.
example.tran: 埃文斯喜不自禁：“我真为她骄傲。”他说。

at 加强 + tain 拿住 → 稳稳拿住 → 获得
attain 获得，达到 + able 能…的 → 可以得到的
attain 获得，达到 + ment 表名词 → 获得的东西 → 成就
con 加强 + tain 拿住 → 统统拿住 → 包含
contain 包含，容纳 + er 表物 → 容器
con 加强 + ten 拿住 + t → 拿住时的量 → 容量，引申为满足的
con 加强 + tin 拿住 + ue → 从头拿到尾 → 继续
con 加强 + tin 拿住 + uous …的，continue的形容词 → 连续不断的
de 加强 + tain 拿住 → 拘留
dis 不 + content 满意的 → 不满的
enter 进入 + tain 拿住 → 在〔工作〕中间抓住时间〔休息〕→ 娱乐
im 不 + pertinent 恰当的；相干的 → 不相干的；无礼的
main 逗留 + tain 拿住 → 留住 → 维持
main 主要的；最重要的（留下的都是精华 → 主要的）+ ten 拿住 + ance，maintain 的名词 → 维护；坚持
ob 加强 + tain 拿住 → 拿到 → 获得
per 自始至终 + tain 拿住 → 始终握住不让两者分开 →〔两者〕从属；相关
per 自始至终 + tin 拿住 + ent 具有…性质的，关于…的 → 始终抓住 → 相干的
re 重新 + tain 拿住 → 重新拿回 → 保留
re 重新 + ten 拿住 + tion，retain 的名词 → 保留；持久力
sus 下 + tain 拿住 → 拿住下面使稳固 → 支持
sus 下，后 + ten 拿住 + ance，sustain 的名词 → 粮食；支持
ten 拿住 + able 能…的 → 能拿住的 → 可守住的
ten 拿住 + acious 有…性质的 → 拿住不放的 → 固执的
ten 拿住 + acity 表状态 → 固执；不屈不挠
ten 拿住 + ant 表人 → 拿〔钱〕租房之人 → 房客
ten 拿住 + ancy 表状况 → 租赁（期限）
ten 拿住 + ure 表结果 → 拿住 → 占有权
un 不 + tenable 可守住的 → 不可防守的
